Kyle Balkissoon at @RinFinance: Extreme News Impacts and Extreme Returns. Are extreme events specific risk? Event-driven: Look at litigation e.g., sentiment (Sentometrics)->returns. Return-driven: find extreme returns, exclude earnings, look at news+sentiment.  #rstats #rfinance

William Foote opens Saturday at @RinFinance: Volatility Spillovers. Using Bayesian priors and Pareto-smoothed importance sampling to find spillovers among green energy ETFs; wind vol->solar vol. #rstats #rfinance
Jay Panchal at @RinFinance: qicR - Quantum Info & Computing in R. About qubits, problems quantum computers can solve, hardware, optimization using quantum computing. #rstats #rfinance

Oliver Delmarcelle at @RinFinance: sentopics - R package for joint sentiment, topic text analysis. Gets sentiment (Loughran-McDonald bag-o-words), topic (like relevance) scores. What drives ECB rate decisions: lately economic conditions dominates monetary policy #rstats #rfinance

Shilin Zhang at @RinFinance: Bankruptcy court competition. Firms shop for pro-debtor venues and judges try to attract cases. She looks at 490 large firms, finds evidence of effects in filings, outcomes, court actions. #rfinance #rstats

Matt Dancho @mdancho84 ⚡️ at @RinFinance: M6 Financial Forecasting Competition - What We've Learned. M6 competition overview; packages: Timetk for time series on tidy, Modeltime=modeling in tidy. https://t.co/wvjTudixqB #rstats #rfinance

David Ardia ⚡️ at @RinFinance: Landscape of academic finance w/structural topic model. Topics favored by journals, over time, increasing participation of women, dominance of top 25 universities at top3-5 journals. #rfinance #rstats

Leopold Catania at @RinFinance: Dynamic multiple quantile (DMQ) models. Maintains quantile monotonicity via updating scheme for conditional quantiles; uses score-driven updating to predict quantiles that do not cross. "Joy Division" plots too! #rstats #rfinance

Chris Thomas at @RinFinance: Pricing Copper Better than Bloomberg - Better than KOSPI levels? Look at returns vs returns in autos, real estate/rebar, aluminum spread as O-U, energy costs (mine+refine), canceled warrants, FX. No more regressing on levels! #rstats #rfinance

Bryan Rodriguez+Luis Arreola at @RinFinance: Space Commodities. Reduced launch costs=>space commodities more relevant. Issues? Fuel=biggest cost, 30-40% of payload. Some firms want to mine asteroids+moon; others: remove debris. Futures? launch costs dominate. #rstats #rfinance

Eden Luvishis + Leonid Maksymenko at @RinFinance: Financial applications of linear risk mgmt via nonlinear ML. Uses accumulated local effects (ALEplot library) to get at nonlinearities of factor exposures across time. https://t.co/BpoaPzd2xD #rstats #rfinance

Paul Teetor @pteetor at @RinFinance: Taming a Portfolio of Spreads. Looks at commodity spreads. Prevailing vol forecasts trade vol. Can forecast drawdown quantiles; need to consider right-censoring. Implies sizing, P(getting stopped out). #rstats #rfinance

Paul Laux at @RinFinance: Learning by lending in the interbank market. Sometimes, banks do not lend overnight to those in need; that's a sign of trouble. VAR shows lenders broaden their network in the area of trouble to learn more. #rstats #rfinance
